title: Understanding the Fill Handle
text: The fill handle is a tool in spreadsheet applications that allows you to quickly fill a series of numbers, dates, or other data types by dragging the corner of a cell.

title: Identifying Patterns
text: When using the fill handle, it's important to recognize patterns in the data. For example, if you start with 'January', the fill handle can continue the series with 'February', 'March', etc.

title: Choosing the Correct Element
text: Consider what type of data series you want to create. If you start with 'January', what would logically follow in a series?
